headline: Gold Has A New Buyer In Town — And The Old Price Rules No Longer Apply
summary: For decades, gold followed a familiar rhythm. Prices rose when fear spiked, fell when calm returned. When gold rallied too far, supply or selling pressure would bring it back down. That framework is now breaking. According to a Goldman Sachs report released Thursday, gold has entered a new phase. Private-sector buyers — not just central banks — are becoming a structural force in price formation.
